dcterms:creator: A. Krizhevsky
dcterms:description: CIFAR10 is a dataset used for training and evaluating machine learning models, particularly in the field of computer vision. It consists of 60,000 32x32 color images in 10 different classes, with 6,000 images per class.
dcterms:title: CIFAR10

dcterms:description: ImageNet is a large-scale dataset used for visual recognition tasks. It contains millions of labeled images across thousands of categories, making it a benchmark for evaluating the performance of image classification algorithms.
dcterms:title: ImageNet
